            "text": "In a co-located office you absorb a huge amount without asking: who looks stressed, which two people are stuck, whether a meeting landed. When your Support team sits in Manila and you sit in the US, all of that ambient information disappears. This is the **visibility gap** — the difference between what you could see in a room and what actually reaches you across distance.\n\nThe wrong response is to rebuild that visibility through constant status pings and surveillance, which erodes trust. The right response is to redesign how work and information flow so the signals you need surface on purpose, not by luck. Distributed management is a design problem before it is a people problem."
