            "heading": "Speak the headline first, then stop",
            "text": "Live communication has no delete key, so **headline-first speaking** matters even more than in writing. Open with your single most important sentence, then pause. The pause signals confidence and lets the executive steer — they'll ask for exactly the depth they want.\n\nMany capable leaders bury their headline because they feel they must justify it first. In a room, that reads as uncertainty. State the conclusion, then support only if asked. Trust that a strong opening line earns you the floor."
