            "text": "Ad-hoc saves don't scale and can't be coached. A **playbook** is a repeatable sequence tied to a churn cause: a failed-onboarding play, an ROI-doubt play, a billing-dispute play, a competitor-shopping play. Each has its own opening, diagnostic questions, and offer boundaries.\n\nThe first move on any at-risk account is choosing the right playbook, which means diagnosing the cause before reaching for a fix. Leading with a discount when the real problem is unused features just trains customers to threaten cancellation for a price cut."
