            "heading": "Role clarity and the handoff to steady state",
            "text": "With teams across the US and Manila, ambiguity about who owns which onboarding step is costly. **Role clarity** — for example, your Manila CSM team owns SMB activation, the US lead owns MidMarket success plans, Support owns break-fix — prevents both gaps and duplicated effort. Remember your Manila team works **US-aligned hours**, so they overlap your business day; the challenge is the night-shift toll on them, not a handoff delay.\n\nOnboarding also has an exit: a deliberate **handoff to steady-state support**. When onboarding completes, the customer should know who to contact next and their context should transfer, so a newly activated realtor isn't stranded when their onboarding CSM steps back."
