            "heading": "Let the network fix the card for you",
            "text": "When a customer's bank reissues a card — new number or new expiry — the card networks keep an updated record. An **account updater** service automatically refreshes the **card-on-file** with the new details before the next charge, so a reissued card never becomes a failed renewal. It is the highest-leverage prevention tool because it fixes expired and reissued cards with zero customer effort.\n\nFor a platform whose customers charge monthly for years, account updater quietly eliminates a large slice of hard declines. If your processor offers it and it isn't enabled, that is often the single biggest fast win in involuntary-churn work."
