            "heading": "The two numbers that matter most",
            "text": "Two metrics anchor the program. Your **failed payment rate** is the share of charges that decline — the size of the inflow you're fighting. Your **recovery rate** is the share of failed charges you win back through prevention plus retries plus dunning. Watched together, they tell you whether the leak is growing and how much of it you're plugging.\n\nSlice both by cause. A rising failed payment rate driven by expired cards points at prevention gaps; a low recovery rate on soft declines points at weak retry or dunning. Aggregate numbers hide the diagnosis; the segmented view tells you which fix to invest in next."
