            "heading": "Billing is a customer touchpoint, not a back office",
            "text": "Every invoice, receipt, and refund is a moment your customer judges Lofty on. For a solo agent paying **$449 a month** out of commission income, a surprise charge or a confusing invoice feels like a broken promise, and they escalate fast. Treating billing as a silent back-office function is how you leak trust and, eventually, revenue.\n\nWhen you run **billing as customer experience**, you design invoices, dunning notices, and refund flows to be clear, timely, and reassuring. The goal is that a customer never has to guess what they paid for or why, because ambiguity is what turns a routine charge into a support ticket and a support ticket into a cancellation."
