            "heading": "The metrics that reveal recoverable revenue",
            "text": "A handful of metrics turn billing from anecdote into strategy. **Recovery rate** is the share of at-risk or failed revenue you actually get back. Alongside it, watch **DSO**, **dispute rate**, **dispute win rate**, and total refunds and credits by reason. Together they show where revenue is leaking and how much of it you're recapturing.\n\nThe point of measuring is comparison over time and across segments. A recovery rate is only meaningful next to last month's and next to what good looks like, so you can tell whether a new dunning sequence or clearer invoice actually moved the number rather than just feeling productive."
