            "heading": "Time and energy are different resources",
            "text": "You can have a free hour and still be unable to think — that is a shortage of **energy**, not **time**. Directors often manage only the calendar and ignore the fact that a strategy memo written at hour ten of back-to-back meetings will be worse than the same memo written fresh. Treating **time vs energy** as one thing is why full calendars still produce shallow output. Later lessons manage each separately; this lesson just names the distinction."
