            "text": "**Energy management** means matching the hardest work to your **peak hours** — the window each day when your focus is naturally sharpest, often the first hours after you start. Doing a churn narrative at your peak and clearing approvals in your afternoon trough gets both done better than the reverse. Most directors do it backwards, spending their sharpest hours on email and their dullest on strategy, then wondering why the strategy is thin."
