            "heading": "An MLS is a private club, not a public utility",
            "text": "A **Multiple Listing Service** is a private, membership-based database run by and for licensed real estate brokers in a given market. It is not a government service and it is not public property — access is a paid privilege tied to holding a real estate license and joining that specific MLS. Your customers are realtors who pay MLS dues on top of what they pay Lofty.\n\nThe reason it exists is simple: a listing broker agrees to share their inventory with every other **broker cooperative** member in exchange for those members bringing buyers. This is the original network effect of real estate — one place where nearly all the for-sale inventory in a market is pooled and searchable."
