            "heading": "Cooperation and compensation",
            "text": "The deal at the heart of an MLS is **cooperation and compensation**: the listing broker offers to cooperate with a buyer's broker and historically advertised an offer of compensation for bringing the buyer. This is what motivates a broker to put their listing into a shared system where competitors can see it.\n\nUnderstanding this deal matters because it explains why listing data is treated as valuable, controlled property rather than open information. Brokers put real economic value into the MLS and expect the rules around who can display and reuse that data to be enforced."
