            "heading": "Speed-to-lead and persistence",
            "text": "Two mechanics do most of the heavy lifting. **Speed-to-lead** means the AI engages within seconds of a lead arriving, when interest is highest — a human agent juggling showings simply cannot match that response time. Persistence means the AI keeps following up over days and weeks on a **nurture cadence**, long after a busy human would have quit.\n\nTogether these convert leads that would otherwise be lost. In coaching customers, this is the sharpest talking point: the AI's edge is not clever copy, it is being instant and tireless at a scale no individual agent can sustain."
